<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="576" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,728,863]" pageId="1" pageNumber="576">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,728,755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="576">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Wings usually present, length variable. Ocellar setae I absent, setae III longer than setae II. Postocular setae 5 pairs. Antennae 7- or 8-segmented, segment I without dorsal apical setae, II with MD setae, III and IV with forked sense-cones, III–VI with microtrichia. Mesosternum with sternopleural suture. Spinula present on mesosternum only. Tarsi 2-segmented. Abdominal tergites VI–VII with paired ctenidia, ctenidia mesad of spiracles on VIII.
</paragraph>
